<item>
            <title>[LU-4921] DNE clients should fall back to &quot;try all stripes&quot; for lookups in directories with unknown hash functions </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4921</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a client gets an LMV for a striped directory with an unknown hash function, the client can fall back to round-robin lookup in all of the stripes instead of just failing outright. The clients already need to do this in case of LMV_HASH_MIGRATE, so it could also be done for unknown hash functions. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
